refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.returnvalues;
On success, this function flushes the result directly to the stdout and returns &true;, &return.falseforfailure;. However, if the CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER option is set, it will return the result on success, &false; on failure.
&return.falseproblem;
Note that response status codes which indicate errors (such as 404 Not found) are not regarded as failure. curl_getinfo can be used to check for these.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Fetching a web page


<?php
// create a new cURL resource
$ch = curl_init();

// set URL and other appropriate options
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, "http://www.example.com/");
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HEADER, 0);

// grab URL and pass it to the browser
curl_exec($ch);

// close cURL resource, and free up system resources
curl_close($ch);
?>
